Title: An Act to Establish Requirements for Warming Shelters
Official Title: An Act to Establish Requirements for Warming Shelters
Number of Sections: 1
Source: versions - Documents and Disposition
Media Type: application/pdf
Strikethrough Detection: 2 sections found

================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1244
H.P. 819 House of Representatives, March 25, 2025
Reference to the Committee on State and Local Government suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative MILLIKEN of Blue Hill.
Cosponsored by Representative: SUPICA of Bangor.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA c. 279 is enacted to read:
3 CHAPTER 279
4 WARMING SHELTERS
5 §1700-F. Warming shelters required
6 A county or municipality in this State shall make available a warming shelter, at an
7 appropriate venue accessible to the public, whenever the temperature is expected to be
8 below 40 degrees Fahrenheit. The warming shelter must be open outside the normal
9 operating hours of the venue providing the warming shelter.
10 SUMMARY
1111 This bill requires each county and municipality in this State to make available a
1122 warming shelter, at an appropriate venue accessible to the public, to be open outside the
1133 normal operating hours of the venue, whenever the temperature is expected to be below 40
1144 degrees Fahrenheit.
Page 1 - 132LR2007(01)
